reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Didn’t want to have buy a whole new dust pan set cause they can be around $20 The strip was one inch longer than needed so I snipped it with some scissors to size. When I went to replace the broken strip, the new one snapped into place for a perfect fit. Hits the floor nice and level so no more having to do repeated brush strokes. Glad it came with two just in case as a backup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Replacement strip works wonders!
reviews.reviewText: I have two cats, and two enclosed litterboxes in the bathrooms. By each litter box, I keep a small child's dustpan to sweep up the litter that makes it outside the box each day. The problem: the dustpan came with no edgestrip (more a toy than a tool) and had a bow in it so would only pick up some of the spilled litter, I had to use a paper towel to get the rest. This replacement edge strip was easy to cut to length (you need tin snips or heavy duty kitchen scissors) then snapped right on to the edge of the dustpan as if it was made for it. One sweep of the little broom and every bit of litter went into the dustpan. Hallelujah!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I wish I could give this zero stars. This was purchased to repair the current dustpan that I have that was perfectly fine except for that piece. I put it on and it fits and stays on great but it does not point down enough to touch the floor. So everything that you sweep into the dustpan goes under it. So I'm currently having to been down and forcibly tilt my long reach dustpan, But this doesn't even work that well. So I have just been sweeping and then using my handheld vacuum.
